{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/linux/update-initramfs-ubuntu","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>In one of my custom linux distors I use a read-only version of the Ubuntu operating system. So, a normal install was copied and compressed into a squashfs image and then <code class=\"language-text\">dd</code>-ed onto the partition.</p>\n<p>It's possible to verify the integrity of that image very quickly during boot with <a href=\"https://www.chromium.org/chromium-os/chromiumos-design-docs/verified-boot-crypto/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">verity</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"verity\" style=\"position:relative;\">Verity<a href=\"#verity\" aria-label=\"verity permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>Before we start, here's an important note that may change your objective and you may not need to all the future steps with altering the initramfs.</p>\n<p>Note: dm-verity is possible without initramfs if the kernel supports it. (<a href=\"https://www.timesys.com/security/dm-verity-without-an-initramfs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Reference</a>. Check it with</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">grep</span> CONFIG_DM_VERITY_VERIFY_ROOTHASH_SIG .config\n<span class=\"token comment\"># CONFIG_DM_VERITY_VERIFY_ROOTHASH_SIG is not set</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>And now, let's proceed with integrating the verity check</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Install <code class=\"language-text\">cryptsetup</code> package (includes <code class=\"language-text\">veritysetup</code>) on the host system</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> <span class=\"token function\">apt</span> update\n<span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> <span class=\"token function\">apt</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> cryptsetup-bin</code></pre></div>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>Add <code class=\"language-text\">dm-verity</code> kernel module to <strong>/etc/initramfs-tools/modules</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">dm-verity</code></pre></div>\n<ol start=\"3\">\n<li>Tell <code class=\"language-text\">initramfs-tools</code> to pack <code class=\"language-text\">veritysetup</code> into the image. Create a file <strong>/etc/initramfs-tools/hooks/veritysetup</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token comment\"># !/bin/sh</span>\n\n<span class=\"token assign-left variable\">PREREQ</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token function-name function\">prereqs</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\">$PREREQ</span>\"</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">case</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$1</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">in</span>\n    prereqs<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n        prereqs\n        <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">exit</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">esac</span>\n\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">.</span> /usr/share/initramfs-tools/hook-functions\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Include veritysetup</span>\ncopy_exec /sbin/veritysetup /sbin\n\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">exit</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span></code></pre></div>\n<ol start=\"4\">\n<li>When a kernel with the appropriate modules will be loaded, the <code class=\"language-text\">init</code> script start executing scripts. Let's define our script that is going to verify the intergrity of the OS. We will use the <a href=\"https://dashdash.io/8/veritysetup\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">open</a> operation for in-kernel verification.</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">mkdir</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-p</span> /etc/initramfs-tools/scripts\n<span class=\"token function\">nano</span> /etc/initramfs-tools/scripts/local-top/verity\n<span class=\"token function\">chmod</span> +x /etc/initramfs-tools/scripts/local-top/verity</code></pre></div>\n<p><strong>/etc/initramfs-tools/scripts/local-top/verity</strong></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token comment\"># !/bin/sh</span>\n\n<span class=\"token assign-left variable\">PREREQ</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token function-name function\">prereqs</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\">$PREREQ</span>\"</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">case</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$1</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">in</span>\n    prereqs<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n        prereqs\n        <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">exit</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">esac</span>\n\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">.</span> /scripts/functions\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Open the root partition with veritysetup</span>\n<span class=\"token assign-left variable\">ROOT_DEV</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"\"</span>\n<span class=\"token assign-left variable\">VERITY_DEV</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"\"</span>\n<span class=\"token assign-left variable\">VERITY_HASH</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token for-or-select variable\">x</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">in</span> <span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token function\">cat</span> /proc/cmdline<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">do</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">case</span> <span class=\"token variable\">${x}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">in</span>\n        <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">systemd.verity_root_data</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>*<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n                <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">value</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token variable\">${x<span class=\"token operator\">#</span>*=}</span>\n                <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">ROOT_DEV</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>/dev/disk/by-uuid/<span class=\"token variable\">${value<span class=\"token operator\">#</span>UUID=}</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n        <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">systemd.verity_root_hash</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>*<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n                <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">value</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token variable\">${x<span class=\"token operator\">#</span>*=}</span>\n                <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">VERITY_DEV</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>/dev/disk/by-uuid/<span class=\"token variable\">${value<span class=\"token operator\">#</span>UUID=}</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n        <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">roothash</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>*<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n                <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">VERITY_HASH</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token variable\">${x<span class=\"token operator\">#</span>*=}</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">esac</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">done</span>\n\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-b</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\">$ROOT_DEV</span>\"</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">||</span> panic <span class=\"token string\">\"Unable to determine root device.\"</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-b</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\">$VERITY_DEV</span>\"</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">||</span> panic <span class=\"token string\">\"Unable to find verity device.\"</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-n</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\">$VERITY_HASH</span>\"</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">||</span> panic <span class=\"token string\">\"No verity hash.\"</span>\n\nveritysetup <span class=\"token function\">open</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\">$ROOT_DEV</span>\"</span> rootfs <span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\">$VERITY_DEV</span>\"</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\">$VERITY_HASH</span>\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-b</span> /dev/mapper/rootfs <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">||</span> panic <span class=\"token string\">\"Verity did not map rootfs.\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">exit</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Be carefull and pay attention that <code class=\"language-text\">veritysetup</code> != <code class=\"language-text\">systemd-veritysetup</code>. systemd version uses the <a href=\"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd-veritysetup@.service.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">attach</a> command (<a href=\"https://man.archlinux.org/man/systemd-veritysetup%40.service.8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">man</a></p>\n<ol start=\"5\">\n<li>Now we are ready to repack the image</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">update-initramfs <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-k</span> <span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token function\">uname</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-r</span><span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-u</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"reference\" style=\"position:relative;\">Reference<a href=\"#reference\" aria-label=\"reference permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.ullright.org/ullWiki/show/initramfs-tools\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">A tutorial</a> for Ubuntu 18.04</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://serverfault.com/questions/152959/configure-initramfs-tools-to-add-curl-to-the-initramfs-and-run-curl-in-a-script\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Add programs to init fs</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://askubuntu.com/questions/1075079/ubuntu-18-04-on-kernel-4-15-0-34-generic-boots-to-busybox\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Add programs #2</a> - cryptsetup</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"dm-verity\" style=\"position:relative;\">dm-verity<a href=\"#dm-verity\" aria-label=\"dm verity permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.chromium.org/chromium-os/chromiumos-design-docs/verified-boot-crypto/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Verified boot specification</a> by Chromium project</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/Dm-verity\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">dm-verity on Arch wiki</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://gitlab.com/cryptsetup/cryptsetup/-/wikis/FrequentlyAskedQuestions#9-the-initrd-question\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">cryptsetup FAQ</a> on gitlab</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/veritytab.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">veritytab manpage</a></li>\n</ul>","excerpt":"In one of my custom linux distors I use a read-only version of the Ubuntu operating system. So, a normal install was copied and compressed…","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#verity\">Verity</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#reference\">Reference</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#dm-verity\">dm-verity</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","fields":{"socialcard":"gatsby-plugin-social-card/7e6878ee-5c9a-5f32-b3e5-2387ad177083.jpg"},"frontmatter":{"date":"June 02, 2023","published":"November 22, 2024","lastModified":"November 22, 2024","title":"Update initramfs","subtitle":"in Ubuntu","section":null,"draft":null,"dev